<hr />
<h2>4 · Explain It 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you show your axolotl on the wall. Talk through it like you are teaching someone who has never seen it. Try to use these words: <strong>x</strong>, <strong>y</strong>, <strong>coordinate</strong>, <strong>across</strong>, <strong>up</strong>, <strong>home spot</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your home spot (the red block) and say why you stand on it every time.</li>
<li>Show your finished axolotl from the front.</li>
<li>Point at one block and read its coordinate out loud: "this one is at x …, y …".</li>
<li>Show one block that you placed in the wrong spot at first, and how you fixed it.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write about 4 sentences for your video.</strong> Plan it here before you record — you can read from it while filming.</p>
